<p>Say I have an XML file with <code>&lt;tag&gt;...&lt;/tag&gt;</code>. I want to be able to query the tag name without regard for case. eg. I want to get <code>&lt;tag&gt;</code> tags, <code>&lt;TAG&gt;</code> tags, etc.</p>  <p><code>$dom-&gt;getElementByTagName()</code> is case-sensitive. It also seems to me that XPath is as well. I tried <code>$xpath-&gt;query("translate(//a, 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ', 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz')")</code> and <code>$xpath-&gt;query("lower-case(//a)")</code> both to no avail.</p>  <p>Any ideas?</p>